In PwnBox SecLists repo available under /opt/useful/SecLists/Discovery/Web-Content/directory-list-... (common words for fuzzing)
* Add a ip to /etc/hosts   sudo sh -c 'echo "SERVER_IP  academy.htb" >> /etc/hosts'
PAGE FUZZING 
|ffuf -s -w /opt/useful/seclists/Discovery/Web-Content/directory-list-2.3-small.txt:FUZZ -u http://83.136.255.159:46527/FUZZ
|     (silent)                     (the text reposotory)                       (place holder)           All to find web pages
|ffuf -w /opt/useful/seclists/Discovery/Web-Content/web-extensions.txt:FUZZ -u http://SERVER_IP:PORT/blog/indexFUZZ
|                                                                        All to find the extensions of pages found previously 
|ffuf -s -w /opt/useful/seclists/Discovery/Web-Content/directory-list-2.3-small.txt:FUZZ -u http://83.136.249.233:49031/blog/FUZZ.php
                                                                All to find the pages inside of & extension of/blog/FUZZ.php
RECURSIVE FUZZING
|ffuf -s -w /opt/useful/seclists/Discovery/Web-Content/directory-list-2.3-small.txt:FUZZ -u 
http://83.136.254.84:56184/FUZZ -recursion -recursion-depth 2 -e .php -v
|                     (recrursive scan)(directories deep)(spesify ext)(view output URLs)
SUB-DOMAIN FUZZING
|ffuf -s -w /opt/useful/seclists/Discovery/DNS/subdomains-top1million-5000.txt:FUZZ -u https://FUZZ.inlanefreight.com/ 
|                                                                                    (look for subdomains)
VHOST FUZZING
|ffuf -s -w /opt/useful/seclists/Discovery/DNS/subdomains-top1million-5000.txt:FUZZ 
-u http://academy.htb:48721/ -H 'Host: FUZZ.academy.htb'
|                    (specify a header) All to scan for VHosts with out manually adding an entire wordlist to /etc/host, we are fuzzing http headers, the host.
FILTERING RESULTS
|ffuf -s -w /opt/useful/seclists/Discovery/DNS/subdomains-top1million-5000.txt:FUZZ 
-u http://academy.htb:48721/ -H 'Host: FUZZ.academy.htb' -ac
|                                              (filters the not founds)
PARAMETER FUZZING -GET
|ffuf -w /opt/useful/seclists/Discovery/Web-Content/burp-parameter-names.txt:FUZZ 
-u http://admin.academy.htb:32248/admin/admin.php?FUZZ=key -ac
                                        (fuzzing ^for the^ parameter needed)
PARAMETER FUZZING -POST
|ffuf -w /opt/useful/seclists/Discovery/Web-Content/burp-parameter-names.txt:FUZZ 
-u http://admin.academy.htb:PORT/admin/admin.php -X POST -d 'FUZZ=key' -H 'Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded'
|curl http://admin.academy.htb:PORT/admin/admin.php -X POST -d 'id=key' -H 'Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded'
                                                                    ^(got from the line above)
VALUE FUZZING

NOTES:
|websites usually have an 'index' as a first subdirectory/path 
